Unfortunately our experience in this hotel was not good.
The rooms are nice enough, and the people in the reception are nice and helpful, HOWEVER:
- Our shower curtain had a huge ugly stain on it. No-should be using such a bathroom.
- Again in the bathroom, there was a big bottle of liquid soap near the shower. It was empty when we got there and was never re-filled (it had some water residue inside it).
- I doubt we were ever given any extra toilet paper during our 3-night stay there. Maybe 1 extra roll. We definitely didn't get any extra paper during the day before the day of our leaving. Only 1 roll left and no extra received.
- There were other weird events that I can't really explain... we got to the room the first night at about 1am and the kids were sleeping until late to make up for that night. The TV somehow went on automatically at 6:30 am. A phone call was received at 8:50am (I quickly hung it up to allow my kids to keep sleeping).
We had lots of things going on at this trip so I didn't bother spending time to complain to the reception about any of this (nor I was asked to provide any feedback), but no-one should be receiving such a service at a Disney hotel, even if it's a 2 stars one. I've actually never received such a service at any hotel I've been to. Hugely disappointing.

Ã‰tant une vague de chaleur, il faisait trÃ¨s chaud dans la chambre et il n'y avait pas de climatisation, ce qui Ã©tait vraiment dommage, je comprends que ce n'est pas si chaud la majoritÃ© de l'annÃ©e, mais c'Ã©tait une grosse dÃ©ception. Notre chambre Ã©tait correcte, nous avons eu quelques petits problÃ¨mes qui ne nous ont pas vraiment dÃ©rangÃ©s, donc je ne ferais pas comme s'ils n'avaient rien fait car nous n'avons alertÃ© l'hÃ´tel qu'en partant afin qu'ils soient au courant avant les prochains habitants de notre chambre, les problÃ¨mes si notre tÃ©lÃ©viseur ne fonctionnait pas, il s'allumerait mais il ne trouverait aucune chaÃ®ne et la fonction SMART TV ne fonctionnait pas. Et l'un de nos tiroirs s'Ã©tait dÃ©tachÃ© des glissiÃ¨res, ce qui le rendait difficile Ã  ouvrir.

Les distributeurs automatiques et les Starbucks de l'hÃ´tel sont chers, plus chers qu'Ã  Disney Park. Une bouteille de coca de 330 ml m'a coÃ»tÃ© 3 euros dans un distributeur automatique et de l'eau de Starbucks Ã  3,80 euros. Conseillez d'aller Ã  l'esso juste Ã  l'extÃ©rieur pour des collations et des boissons moins chÃ¨res. Nous avons pris nos collations et nos boissons dans un supermarchÃ© Ã  Paris lorsque nous sommes allÃ©s faire du tourisme un jour de notre voyage. 6 bouteilles d'eau de 1,5L pour 1,35 euros. Aubaine. Malheureusement, la chambre n'avait pas de rÃ©frigÃ©rateur pour les garder au frais, donc ce n'Ã©tait pas l'eau la plus fraÃ®che quand nous en avions besoin.
J'ai remarquÃ© qu'il y avait beaucoup de places de stationnement Ã  l'hÃ´tel, moi et mon partenaire avons l'intention de conduire du Royaume-Uni la prochaine fois (nous avons pris l'avion cette fois - vacances Ã  forfait), donc c'est agrÃ©able de savoir que nous avons des options de stationnement pour notre arrivÃ©e.
TrÃ¨s reconnaissant pour la navette gratuite, c'est juste dommage que tout le monde se batte pour Ã§a, ils pourraient peut-Ãªtre faire fonctionner un bus supplÃ©mentaire aux heures de pointe (seulement 1) ou crÃ©er un systÃ¨me de file d'attente alors que les gens deviennent des animaux essayant de monter sur le bus quand il y a du mondeÂ ! La navette Ã©tait courte de toute faÃ§on environ 5 minutes.

(Avis d'origine)
Me and my partner had a 3 night stay at Hotel Sana Fe 11th-14th August. It was very hot these 4 days, a heatwave at 35 degrees.
When we arrived our room was ready, quick and easy check in and got our Magic Cards and got directed. Very friendly staff with good english. We were in the luigi section which was a bit of the shame as its nicer/easier to tell people you stayed in the Lightning Mcqueen part but it is what it is!
Being a heatwave it was very hot in the room and there was no A/C which was a big shame, I understand its not that hot the majority of the year but it was a big let down. We did have a ceiling fan but this didnt really do much for us.
Our room was decent, we had a couple of little issues that didnt really bother us so I wont make it out like they didnt do anything because we only alerted the hotel when leaving so they were aware before the next habitants of our room, the issues were our TV didnt work it would turn on but it would not find any channels and the SMART TV function didnt work. And one of our drawers had come off of the runners making it awkward to open.
Food was good, we only ever had breakfast at the hotel so the options for breakfast were very varied, the queue moved pretty quick too.
The vending machines and starbucks in the hotel are expensive, more expensive than in disney park. A 330ml coke bottle cost me 3 euros from a vending machine and some water from starbucks was 3.80 euros. Advise going to the esso just outside for cheaper snacks and drinks. We got our snacks and drinks from a supermarket in Paris when we went sightseeing one day of our trip. 6x1.5L bottles of water for 1.35 euros. Bargain. Unfortunately the room had no fridge to keep them cool so it was not the coolest water when we needed it.
I noticed theres plenty of parking at the hotel, me and my partner are intending to drive from the UK next time (we flew this time - package holiday) so its nice to know we have parking options for when we arrive.
Very greatful for the free shuttle bus, its just a shame everybody fights over it, they maybe could do with running an extra bus in peak times (only appeared to be 1) or make a queue system as people become animals trying to get onto the bus when busy! Shuttle was short anyway about 5 mins.
Overall the hotel is good but advise buying snacks/drinks from elsewhere and would be nice to have air conditioned rooms.

Few points to note:
1. Basic amenities of a decent hotel are missing like no fridge, microwave, coffee machine, kettle, in the room.
2. You have nearly no alternatives to food apart from what you bring or what is offered in their limited restaurants
3. Outside food cannot be ordered to your room.
4. Pillows gave me a sore neck
5. Rooms are too small you can never stay with kids in one room both beds occupy 90% of the space
6. If you are planning to take their free shuttle service be prepared to walk half a mile with your kids to reach the pickup point, Disney if you want to call it an hotel have some decency to have shuttle pickup done from at least 3 points far left, far right and the current centre
7. The baggage drop is always crowded, if you are planning to drop your baggage and head straight to Disneyland consider delays like 15 minimum due to this.
8. At this price point the so called hotel doesn't even offer a basic availability of enough staff, the parks close at 23:00 and if you are pending with your check-in or something, god help you, as there will be 1 receptionist at a counter where at least 10 can be there and already fed with queues in the park, you will land in a new queue all exhausted.
9. No air conditioning so in hot sunny days good luck with the ceiling fan that makes noise the whole night, well that was not the only thing that makes noise, the other were entry door and bathroom door.

De l'extÃ©rieur, il a l'air trÃ¨s basique, il y a un thÃ¨me (sur le thÃ¨me du Nouveau-Mexique / des voitures), l'hÃ´tel est divisÃ© en blocs rÃ©partis sur le site. Il y a une petite boutique sur place vendant des produits Disney et des rafraÃ®chissements ainsi qu'un restaurant et un Starbucks.
Quant aux chambres, elles sont trÃ¨s basiques mais ce Ã  quoi on s'attend pour ce type d'hÃ´tel. Si vous avez sÃ©journÃ© Ã  Disney World en Floride, ils sont comparables aux hÃ´tels de valeur (Pop Century, Art of Animation et All-stars).
Il y a une longue marche Ã  pied vers les parcs, donc si vous voyagez avec de jeunes enfants ou avez des problÃ¨mes de mobilitÃ©, gardez cela Ã  l'esprit, il y a des navettes qui vous emmÃ¨nent aux parcs, mais si vous marchez, attendez-vous Ã  un 20 minutes Ã  pied de cet hÃ´tel.
Dans l'ensemble, si vous avez un budget limitÃ© ou si vous ne vous souciez pas vraiment de l'endroit oÃ¹ vous sÃ©journez, c'est une bonne option, mais pour un prix et un emplacement similaires, vous pouvez opter pour l'hÃ´tel Cheyenne qui, personnellement, je pense qu'il a un meilleur thÃ¨me et une ambiance plus agrÃ©able Ã  propos de il.

Hotel Santa Fe is a budget Disney hotel, I did not stay here as I had been staying at Newport Bay Club hotel but we had family staying at Santa Fe during our visit so I got to see the hotel and the rooms.
From the outside, it looks very basic, it does have theming (New Mexico/Cars themed) the hotel is divided into blocks which are spread across the site. There is a small shop on site selling Disney merchandise and refreshments as well as a restaurant and a Starbucks.
As for the rooms, they are very basic but what you would expect for this type of hotel. If youâ€™ve stayed in Disney World in Florida then theyâ€™re comparable to the value resorts (Pop Century, Art of Animation and All-stars).
There is a bit of a long walk to the parks so if youâ€™re travelling with young children or have mobility issues then bare that in mind, there are shuttle buses which take you to the the parks but if youâ€™re walking, expect a 20 minute walk from this hotel.
Overall, if youâ€™re on a budget or not really fussed about where you are staying then this is a good option, however for a similar price and location you could opt for Hotel Cheyenne which personally i feel has better theming and a nicer vibe about it.

Stayed here a couple of times because it was one of the cheaper stays. Very clean hotel with friendly staff. Great bar, gift shop and all you can eat evening buffet ( some great vegan, veggie options too!) Didn't eat at breakfast times so can't rate this.
Rooms are done in the theme of Cars and was spacious with 2 double beds, hair dryer, safe and toiletries.
In the evenings 2 characters (Mickey and friends) alternate giving you chance to meet, greet and get photos. Masks were still needed indoors when having photos.
Short walk to Disney village/parks.
Would stay again if on a budget but if you can afford a bit more, the Sequoia is next door and has a swimming pool.

The hotel staff speak English for the most part so communication is easy. The staff was helpful and friendly. It is the economical choice however if you are on a budget.

Pro:

Contre:
-L'hÃ´tel est vieux, a besoin d'Ãªtre rÃ©novÃ©.
-Le personnel ne parle principalement que le franÃ§ais
-Pas trÃ¨s sympathique et parfois pas disposÃ© Ã  aider
(Avis d'origine)
We stayed here 2 nights, 3 days and had access to the parc for 3 days.
Check-in:
We finally arrived at Santa Fe and we wanted to check-in directly so we could go to the parc. We walked in and directly a man was talking French and later English to us. We were wondering who this man was but later we noticed that he was working for Disney. We could not see that he was working for Disney as it looks like he was wearing his own clothes. He pointed out that we should walk to his colleague. His colleague was asking us something but she couldn't speak English that well. So we were really trying to understand her as she got annoyed and send us to another colleague. This colleague spoke English and we understood her.
Hotel
Finally checked-in we could parked for free at the hotel building itself. We took our stuff and walked to our rooms. The rooms are old looking, bathroom had mold and could use some renovation. But who stays in the room f you are in Disney so we took it for granted.
Stay:
We had half board and had our dinner in La Cantina. The worst food in the evening you can get there. No other guests were there. Personnel was just al standing together and talking to each other. Not good in etiquette. Direct after finishing our plate, asking if we wanted more food. They were constantly looking from 5 meters away if we were done eating. I would not recommend the terrine. It is horrible - looks like dog food.
Also the mention it is all you can eat but there are only 3 options in starter, 3 options in main course and 3 options in dessert.
Extra:
If you buy accessories from the parc you can choose for free delivery to the hotel. We recommend doing that so you do not have to carry everything. Pick it up after 8 pm at the hotel store. We were a little late back in the hotel and the next day was our check-out. Apparently the store opens at 4 pm to pick up your bought accessories. So we asked the reception to please get it for us because of our 7,5h drive. There answer was no and it was not possible. Later we asked someone else and suddenly it was possible.
Pro:
-cheaper
-some personnel is friendly
-Breakfast is good
-free parking
-easy bus access from hotel to parc
Con:
-Hotel is old, needs to be renovated.
-Personnel can mostly only speak French
-Not very friendly and sometimes not willing to help

Check in was a nightmare, best part of two hours to get our tickets and meal plan sorted. This was especially frustrating after we were asked to return to the reception later to gain access to our rooms. However staff were incredibly polite and helpful considering how demanding their work seems. The room itself was clean, compact but basic in what it offered, tea and coffee would be a nice addition but i imagine it would dissuade potential customers from their onsite Starbucks. The hotel is a short 10-15min walk from the parks and the shuttle buses are regular although they are a squeeze to get on. ReviewText:
If you are looking for a budget hotel that is on site at Disney you are looking in the right place. But only if Cheyenne is fully booked. We came here in September during the Run weekend so it was busy.
The rooms were clean but they lacked one major thing, air conditioning or a window that you could get some sort of air through, the room we had seemed to trap heat no matter what you did and it made it almost unbearable to be in during the day so keep that in mind if you have kids.
The Hotel its self is well themed and maintained as you would expect from any Disney hotel and the gift shop and restaurants were good. The on site restaurant is a all you can eat buffet which we didn't end up going too as we felt we were never hungry enough. Be warned the line for the Breakfast at this hotel is VERY long. The bar has small snacks and drinks which was where we ended up going, again another lovely themed bar with nice drinks for adults and kids alike and nice bar food with a Mexican feel.
When it comes to this hotel the only reason it didn't get the full 5 stars was simply down to the heat of the room and that I clearly have been spoiled by Cheyenne next door. The walk to the parks is easy just be prepared in the summer months to sweat more in your rooms that outside.

Name: P Borthwick
ReviewText:
We are just back from a long weekend at this hotel. We had to queue for an hour to check it. Our room was clean, but was in need of serious upgrading. Bathroom grout missing, toilet was brown and kept making a running noise. Walls and furniture was damaged, room was freezing. We eventually figured out how to work the radiator and rooms are dark and small. Towels are tiny and well used and in need of replacement. We booked in for dinner on two nights and given a slot of 6 pm. Utterly pointless as the queue for dinner was out the door and 25 min later you were through then queuing again to be seated. Same farce at breakfast time. Food was terrible. Bland, tasteless, chicken was pink inside. Not enough choice for kids. No nuggets or fish fingers things you expect. You are asked what you want to drink on arrival and then collect from bar, and at breakfast the glasses are tiny! Same with plates itâ€™s all very stingy! Staff were unhelpful, borderline rude at times. The tiny kids zone at dinner was just silly really, no colouring in for the kids to do and same out at reception, a small table with pencils but no paper. I had to ask at reception for some paper for the kids and was given 3 bits! Silly! Kicked out room at 11 am so had to queue 30 min to put suitcase in the baggage room. Always a queue to get the shuttle to the park. We had the buggy and people were so rude pushing you and past you, standing in the area for the buggy and not moving. Queues at park were ridiculous and that was just to get through the scanner and security. We had terrible rain aswell which is one of those things that canâ€™t be helped.But we wonâ€™t be back to this hotel or Paris. We were really put off by the ignorant and rude French people Who we encountered on our trip. Even in the park people dressed up as characters would just leave or walk away after you had queued for ages and they would say oh they donâ€™t stay long. I was left explaining to a 3 year old. The Mc Donaldâ€™s in the Disney village was a joke too! 50 min wait to get food. The park to me felt dirty, and smelly in areas like sewage . My advice save up your money and take your kids to Florida! Where they will have the best time! The Americans canâ€™t do enough for you! And itâ€™s a different level. Disney Paris was not magical for us! And left us utterly disappointed!
